China’s Inflation Rate to Slow, Xinhua Says, Citing Forecaster

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-06-25T13:58:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-25/china-s-inflation-rate-to-slow-xinhua-says-citing-forecaster.html
China ’s inflation rate is
“controllable” and prices will fall in the second half of the
year, the Xinhua  News Agency  said, citing Fan Jianping, director
of economic forecasting at the State Information Center.  Inflation will slow after the end of June as food and house
prices stabilize, the news agency cited Jianping as saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
